BNB Hack Announces Latest Round of Winning Projects: Basement, DeFi Copilot, BIBIMBNB Chain has announced the latest batch (6/23–7/17) of BNB Hack selection results. Social protocol Basement (DeSoc direction), AI-powered DeFi assistant DeFi Copilot, and strategy tool BIBIM (AI direction) have successfully received awards, each receiving a 3,000.00 USDT prize, a 50,000 Kickstart reward package, and an official Demo Day presentation opportunity. At the same time, AI-oriented Peridot and Agent Einstein have been added to the incubation observation list.
This round received over 30 submissions from global developers, including those from the New York offline event:
Basement: Provides an instant social layer for web pages, combined with AI Agent, to achieve one-click chat, interaction, rewards, and information aggregation;
DeFi Copilot: A one-stop PancakeSwap trading assistant that integrates real-time analysis, one-click order placement, and automatic management;
BIBIM: Simplifies strategy construction, testing, and monetization with a visual interface and AI, reducing DeFi complexity;
BNB Hack is a long-term hackathon launched by BNB Chain targeting Web3 innovation directions such as AI, DeSoc, DeSci, and DePIN. It has currently received over 200 global submissions and has cumulatively selected 9 Tier 3 projects and 40 potential projects. [Odaily]

